---

<Base title="About" description="What OwnPulse is, why it exists, and how the cooperative model works.">
  <!-- Mission -->
  <section class="py-20 md:py-28 bg-surface-elevated">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-neutral-900 font-display">Health data that works for you</h1>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-lg text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Your health data is scattered across a dozen apps, each with its own export format, its own
          terms of service, and its own incentive to keep you locked in. Most of them sell aggregate
          data to insurers and researchers — you never see the value.
        </p>
        <p>
          OwnPulse is a cooperative: a platform owned and governed by its members. It collects every
          meaningful health signal — wearables, labs, interventions, subjective check-ins — and puts
          them on a single timeline you control. The code is open source. The data schema is public
          domain. You can self-host on a $6/month VPS or use the cooperative-hosted tier.
        </p>
        <p>
          When members choose to share anonymized data for research, 80% of the revenue flows back to
          them as hosting credits or charitable donations. The other 20% covers cooperative operating
          costs. There are no investors to extract value. The board is elected by members. The
          architecture is designed so that even if the cooperative disappears, your data remains yours
          — fully exportable in open formats.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is not a health app that happens to be open source. It's health data infrastructure
          built from the ground up for sovereignty, portability, and collective benefit.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What OwnPulse tracks -->
  <section class="py-20 md:py-28 bg-surface">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 font-display">What OwnPulse tracks</h2>

      <div class="mt-10 grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-800">Wearables &amp; devices</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
            HRV, resting heart rate, sleep stages, SpO2, weight, blood pressure, VO2 max, training
            load, continuous glucose, skin temperature deviation. Syncs from Apple HealthKit, Garmin,
            Oura, and Dexcom.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-800">Interventions</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
            Medications, supplements, peptides, nootropics — substance, dose, unit, route, timing,
            fasted state. The platform is non-judgmental: all interventions are legitimate data. No
            validation or warnings on substance names.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-800">Subjective check-ins</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
            Five daily scores (1-10): energy, mood, focus, recovery, libido. Takes less than 30
            seconds. Over time, these correlate with objective metrics in ways that surprise you.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-800">Labs</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
            Blood panel data with reference ranges. Upload PDFs from Quest or LabCorp, or enter
            results manually. Track markers over time with trend lines and out-of-range flagging.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-800">Calendar</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
            Meeting count and minutes per day from Google Calendar. Meeting load is health data —
            correlate it with HRV, sleep, and energy.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-800">Observations</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
            Events (cold plunge, sauna, injury), custom scales (pain, stress), symptoms (brain fog,
            headache), context tags (travel, altitude), environmental data (temperature, AQI), and
            freeform notes. Fully user-defined — no waiting for a schema update.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The cooperative model -->
  <section class="py-20 md:py-28 bg-surface-elevated">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 font-display">The cooperative model</h2>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-lg text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          OwnPulse operates as a data cooperative under a nonprofit structure. There are two ways
          to use it: self-host on your own server (any Linux VPS with 2GB RAM) or use the
          cooperative-hosted tier. Both use the same code, the same Helm charts, the same data
          format.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you use the cooperative-hosted tier, you can opt in to contribute anonymized data to a
          research marketplace — per dataset, granular, revocable at any time. Genetic data requires
          a separate, stricter consent. The anonymization standard uses k-anonymity (k&ge;50),
          differential privacy, and weekly-resolution aggregates. Researchers get aggregate query
          access only — never raw exports.
        </p>
        <p>
          When cooperative data is sold to researchers, 80% of the revenue is distributed to
          consenting members as hosting credits or charitable donations. The remaining 20% covers
          infrastructure and operating costs. There are no shareholders, no venture capital, no
          exit strategy that involves selling your data.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Privacy by design -->
  <section class="py-20 md:py-28 bg-surface">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 font-display">Privacy by design</h2>

      <ul class="mt-10 space-y-5 text-lg text-neutral-600">
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold shrink-0">&mdash;</span>
          <span>Data stored on your infrastructure (self-hosted) or your chosen region (cooperative hosted).</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold shrink-0">&mdash;</span>
          <span>Full export anytime — JSON, CSV, FHIR R4. No friction, no delay.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold shrink-0">&mdash;</span>
          <span>GDPR, CCPA, and PIPEDA compliant. Data subject rights implemented as API endpoints.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold shrink-0">&mdash;</span>
          <span>User-held encryption keys on the cooperative hosted tier.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold shrink-0">&mdash;</span>
          <span>No analytics. No telemetry. No phone-home behavior. Zero tracking.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Built in the open -->
  <section class="py-20 md:py-28 bg-surface-elevated">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 font-display">Built in the open</h2>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-lg text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          <strong class="text-neutral-800">AGPL-3.0</strong> — any company offering OwnPulse as a
          hosted service must publish their modifications. Improvements flow back to the community.
          You can audit every line of code that touches your health data.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-neutral-800">Open data schema (CC0)</strong> — the export format is
          public domain. Any application can read an OwnPulse export without license obligation.
          Your data is never locked in a proprietary format.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-neutral-800">Public architecture decisions</strong> — every
          significant technical choice is documented as an Architecture Decision Record in the
          repository. Read why we chose Rust, why AGPL, why Kubernetes, why this testing strategy.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-neutral-800">Cooperative governance</strong> — the community elects
          board seats. One member, one vote. No class of shares that concentrates control.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Team / founding -->
  <section class="py-20 md:py-28 bg-surface">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 font-display">Who's building this</h2>

      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
        OwnPulse is early stage. Built by a small team who got tired of their health data being
        someone else's asset. We track peptides, supplements, and biomarkers — and we wanted a
        platform that treats all of that as legitimate data without judgment, on infrastructure we
        control, with a data format we can take anywhere.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
        If that resonates, <a href="#waitlist" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-dark underline">join the waitlist</a>
        or <a href="https://github.com/ownpulse/ownpulse" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-dark underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">contribute on GitHub</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
